abstract_ssm: The collection consists of a document recording the naturalization in the County Court of Kings County, New York on October 13, 1857 of John Comyns, a teenaged Irish immigrant living in Brooklyn, New York.  Included are two sworn oaths and a certification by a county clerk in 1894 of the authenticity of the copy of the record.
